results.lead_paragraph: They were poked and prodded everywhere and X-rayed 75 times. They had ice water injected into their ears to test their balance. They were spun, dunked, entombed and advised to put off having children in case space duty called. Training in secret, 13 female pilots passed the grueling physical examinations for astronauts in the early 1960's, proving they did indeed have as much of the right stuff as the men chosen for the Mercury 7 program, which was being prepared at the same time.
